<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: ANAHEIM; 
</P>
<P>
OPERATOR INJURED WHEN HIS CRANE FALLS OVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 52-year-old man was listed in stable condition at UCI Medical Center after he 
leaped from a toppling crane Wednesday morning while working on a sewer 
reconstruction project. 
</P>
<P>
The man, whose name was being withheld until relatives were notified, was 
working with an independent contractor on the city's project in the 1600 block 
of West Ball Road, according to Fire Chief Steve Magliocco. Officials said they 
were uncertain where the man lived and whether he was self-employed. 
</P>
<P>
Magliocco said the man was operating the crane off the back of a flatbed truck 
at 7:56 a.m. When he attempted to move a large pipe into a ditch, the crane 
tipped over. 
</P>
<P>
The operator jumped from the crane in the opposite direction and fell about 10 
feet to the ground. He suffered minor injuries to his knees and one of his 
arms, Magliocco said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
