126 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY; 
</P>
<P>
OLMOS WINS IMAGE AWARD FROM GROUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Hollywood chapter of the Hispanic Academy of Media Arts and Sciences 
announced that actor-producer Edward James Olmos is the first recipient of its 
new award -- the first annual HAMAS Award for the Positive Image of Hispanics. 
</P>
<P>
Olmos was honored for his humanitarian and charitable work, as well as his 
portrayal of Garfield High School teacher Jaime Escalante in "Stand and 
Deliver." 
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the fifth annual Imagen Hispanic Media Image Awards -- to encourage 
positive images of Latinos and reduce stereotyping in television and film -- 
will be given by the National Conference of Christians and Jews in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
May 15 is the deadline for submitting films, television episodes and TV movies 
for consideration. Information: (213) 385-0491. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA050489-0030 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 52242 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
May 4, 1989, Thursday, Nuestro Tiempo Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
