<P>
HAILSTORMS KILL 157 IN CHINA OVER 10 DAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BEIJING 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hailstorms that battered wide areas of southwest Sichuan province over a 10-day 
period killed 157 people and injured 6,000, the newspaper China Daily said 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
The storms, which hit 105 of the province's 175 counties from April 20 through 
last week, also destroyed 170,000 houses, the English-language newspaper said. 
Earlier reports had put the death toll from the storms at 87. 
</P>
