<HEADLINE>
<P>
'HEROIC' PARKING BUST CRITICIZED. . .; 
</P>
<P>
. . .BUT 'SCOFFLAWS' TAKE LUMPS TOO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Scofflaw: flouting the law" -- Webster's. 
</P>
<P>
These scofflaws not only flouted the law, but they did so with very selfish 
motives: They also, in flouting the law, very selfishly deprived other 
motorists of the right to park in the obviously crowded Malaga Cove shopping 
plaza. 
</P>
<P>
Their acts, while not criminal, were offenses against society as a whole -- and 
they justly deserve whatever punishment the courts mete out. 
</P>
<P>
Inconsiderate, selfish people comprise the greater number of scofflaws, whose 
only interests are self-interests . . . and the public be damned. 
</P>
<P>
Kudos to the law enforcement officers who took the necessary steps to insure 
fairness overall. 
</P>
<P>
CLINT HOWARD 
</P>
<P>
Gardena 
</P>
