<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: NORWALK; 
</P>
<P>
AGENCY VOTES FUNDS TO HELP REMODEL SHOPPING CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Norwalk Redevelopment Agency on Tuesday voted to spend up to $550,000 to 
assist in the remodeling of the Norwalk Square shopping center. 
</P>
<P>
West Venture Development Co., which owns the shopping center, plans to remodel 
all buildings facing Pioneer Boulevard and Rosecrans Avenue using a Spanish 
architectural theme. West Venture also plans to build a multiscreen theater and 
an 8,140-square-foot commercial building on the site. 
</P>
<P>
The retail shopping center is one of the key projects in the city's plans to 
develop a Spanish-style village, of sorts, along San Antonio Drive from the 
Santa Ana Freeway to Rosecrans. The city plans to use redevelopment and federal 
grant money. 
</P>
<P>
A report by Donald J. Rouly, Norwalk director of economic development, said 
some details of the project still have to be worked out, but that the agency 
would contribute up to $550,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
