<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: AZUSA; 
</P>
<P>
TORRES OPPOSES EXPANSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rep. Esteban E. Torres (D-La Puente) has joined San Gabriel Valley water 
agencies in urging the state Water Resources Control Board to reject a permit 
for expansion of the Azusa Land Reclamation Co.'s landfill in Azusa. 
</P>
<P>
"The proposed site is not suited for a landfill since ground-water sources are 
located directly under the area and are used for the drinking needs of the 
residents," Torres said. 
</P>
<P>
The Los Angeles Regional Water Quality Control Board approved a permit last 
year for disposal in new areas of the landfill under conditions that would 
require the use of clay soil and a plastic liner to keep contaminants from 
seeping into ground water. But the San Gabriel Valley Watermaster, an 
organization that allocates the use of ground water in the Main San Gabriel 
Basin, appealed the decision to the state board. The board's staff has 
recommended that the regional decision be overturned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
