<P>
Drabinsky Seeks New Partners: Garth Drabinsky, chairman of Cineplex Odeon, said 
he will try to form an investment group to make a tender offer for an 
unspecified number of shares of the Toronto-based movie theater company. A deal 
for an earlier Drabinsky group to buy a 30% interest from the Charles R. 
Bronfman family of Canada was abandoned last week after it was opposed by 
Canadian securities regulators and MCA, which owns 49% of Cineplex. Drabinsky 
and Cineplex Vice Chairman Myron I. Gottlieb said in a filing with the 
Securities and Exchange Commission that they will solicit former group members 
and "other persons, firms and corporations" about forming the new group. 
