<HEADLINE>
<P>
RAMS FIRST-ROUND DRAFT PICK HAS EYES ON BASEBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ATLANTA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Atlanta Braves confirmed today that they have held talks with Cleveland 
Gary, a Rams first-round draft pick who says he wants to play baseball. 
</P>
<P>
"We have talked with Gary and his agent," said Braves spokesman Jim Schultz, 
adding that he did not know whether Gary was close to being signed. 
</P>
<P>
Gary, a fullback who finished his college football career at Miami after 
transferring from Georgia in 1985, told WTVX-TV in West Palm Beach, Fla., that 
he is "definitely interested in a career in professional baseball." 
</P>
<P>
"I tried out for the Braves for three days about a month ago," he said. "They 
wanted to sign me right away." 
</P>
